<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="c0d3f222-671a-5008-bf83-175f9ad5c625" activityNameId="1a7d4baa-5a0d-49d4-a9fb-26ae0fa5c707" parentActivityId="a0146dd1-5c65-4dcf-8234-565f6a716148" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1" energyValues="0">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">beverage carton production, 1 L, for UHT milk (ambient)</activityName>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">This activity starts at the gate of the facility for sleeve and closure/neck production with the reception of raw materials.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">The activity ends with the produced beverage cartons as well as neck and closure being ready for transportation to filler. This activity includes the production of beverage cartons for UHT milk packaging. It contains the steps of laminating, cutting, folding and printing as well as cap production. Besides the main raw materials (LPB, LDPE, HDPE, PP and aluminium), ink is considered too. It does not include forming, filling and sealing which need to be modelled in a separate dataset. Production waste is modelled as two separate exchanges, waste paperboard (unsorted) and mixed waste specifically from beverage carton production.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This activity represents the production of sleeve and closure/neck of one beverage carton for UHT (ultra high temperature processed) milk stored in ambient temperature. The beverage carton's volume is 1 L and its mass is 30.74 g. A standard 1 L carton has an area of 0.07889 m². The dataset describes only the actual production of the sleeve and closure of the beverage carton for UHT milk packaging. Sleeve and closure/neck production take place on different production sites.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1"></text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">Beverage cartons are made of LPB (liquid packaging board) which is coated with plastic resins and often laminated for product protection and extended shelf life. In the modelled beverage carton there are two parts, carton body and plastic closure and neck. The body is made of LPB, LDPE (light density polyethylene) and aluminium. The closure and neck are made of HDPE (high density polyethylene) and PP (polypropylene). The energy inputs to the process are modeled via the services injection moulding, beverage carton converting and sheet rolling, aluminium. </text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3"></text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="4">The scrap rate of the production process of the carton body is 5.33 %. Hence, the inputs contributing to carton body have been divided by (1-0.0533). The processing of materials used in closure and neck is modelled by injection moulding, which takes into account the losses of these inputs.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="5"></text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="6">The filling process (including forming and sealing of the filled beverage cartons) as well as packaging of filled beverage cartons for distribution to retailers is not modelled in the dataset. However, the following data can be used to model the secondary and tertiary packaging needed to retail the UHT milk cartons: The beverage cartons are transported on pallets. The pallet specification is: 10 packs per tray, 15 trays per layer and 5 layers per pallet. Thus, the pallet can be used to transport 10 x 15 x 5 = 750 empty UHT milk cartons at a time. The cardboard tray as secondary packaging has a mass of 0.115 kg. In tertiary packaging of the pallet, 0.170 kg of shrink foil and 0.475 kg of slip sheet is used. A pallet has a mass of 25 kg. When all the packaging materials are considered, the pallet with empty UHT milk cartons has a total mass of 57.2 kg.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="7"></text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="8">The dataset is based on an LCA study on beverage cartons in the European market conducted by the data provider IFEU (Institut für Energie- und Umweltforschung). The data for the study was provided by the members of ACE (The Alliance for Beverage Cartons and the Environment). The data in this inventory represent an average production of a beverage carton for UHT milk packaging and the dataset itself has a broad application. Hence, it does not represent a specific or particular beverage packaging. If you are conducting life cycle assessment of specific beverage carton (packaging) it is advised to collect more specific data about detailed material composition of the product in question since this information can vary greatly between beverage cartons.</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="fa432e96-bb87-4aff-939d-46929ee9be72">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">EcoSpold01Categories</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">paper &amp; cardboard/cardboard &amp; corrugated board</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <classification classificationId="5682ee05-067a-4dd3-a2b5-93f3f1d25c75">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">1702:Manufacture of corrugated paper and paperboard and of containers of paper a</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="0723d252-7e2a-11de-9820-0019e336be3a">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">RER</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The data is for beverage beverage cartons produced and used in Europe.</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Current installed at specified time. The dataset is applicable for both, sleeve based and roll based, production processes.</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2017-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The reference period of the dataset is the year 2017.</text>
        </comment>
      </timePeriod>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
